# Server Package (`@navo/server`)

## Entry Points

- Boot: `server/src/index.ts` — HTTP + WS + FCM + scheduler
- REST: `server/src/http.ts` — Express routes
- Real-time: `server/src/ws.ts` — WebSocket hub, `ServerEvent` dispatch
- WebRTC: `server/src/sfu.ts` — SFU for calls
- Data: `server/src/db.ts` (MySQL), `server/src/redis.ts` (pub/sub, presence)

## Key Modules

| Module | Role |
|--------|------|
| `auth.ts` | JWT, login, registration |
| `admin-routes.ts` | Admin REST API |
| `ai.ts` | AI chat integration |
| `config.ts` | Env vars from root `.env` |
| `verification.ts` | Email/SMS verification |
| `scheduler.ts` | Scheduled message delivery |

## Conventions

- ES modules with `.js` extension in imports (e.g. `import { x } from './db.js'`)
- All functions need type annotations; comments in Simplified Chinese
- `db.ts` runs migrations on import — must load before server starts
- Redis keys prefixed with `navo:im:`

## Doc Reference

Read `docs-src/server/src/<module>.md` before editing `server/src/<module>.ts`.
